net.krotscheck.jersey2.http.header

Class AcceptsHeader

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.http.message.BasicHeader
      • net.krotscheck.jersey2.http.header.AcceptsHeader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, org.apache.http.Header

    public final class AcceptsHeader
extends org.apache.http.message.BasicHeader
    The factory converts the raw HTTP Accept header into a BasicHeader collection of individual header elements, which are sorted based on priority. It is injected into the context as a Named entity using the header as its name.
    Author:
    Michael Krotscheck
